Manufacturing

From tooling to finished parts.
Telamorph manufactures advanced composite components through controlled processes, modern equipment and a production mindset built around repeatability.
Vacuum infusion, prepreg processing, compression molding, bonding, assembly and post-processing are selected around the part — not forced into a single method.
The goal is simple: composite parts that meet the requirements and can be produced again with confidence.
Visual direction:
Hero section with a strong production image: mold, carbon layup, finished part, or clean workshop scene. Dark, precise, high-end. Avoid a chaotic factory feeling.
________________________________________
Production begins with the tool.
The quality of a composite part starts before the material is placed.
Tooling, molds, master models and supporting fixtures are prepared according to the geometry, surface requirements and expected production volume. Every production route is built to support accuracy, reliability and control.
Catch phrase:
The mold defines the part.
Visual direction:
Show tooling surfaces, CNC-machined forms, master models, molds or jig setups. Clean lighting. The image should feel engineered, not handmade.
________________________________________
Built through the right process.
Different parts require different production routes.
Vacuum infusion, prepreg, compression molding and selected curing processes allow the structure, surface quality and production to meet the requirements of the component.
Catch phrase:
The method follows the part.
Visual direction:
Process-focused visuals: infusion setup, prepreg layup, mold closing, oven curing. Keep the photography clean and selective.
________________________________________
Finished means ready.
Manufacturing does not end when the part leaves the mold.
Trimming, milling, curing, bonding, assembly, surface preparation, coating and painting can all be part of the final production route. The result is a component prepared for use, installation or integration into a larger system.
Catch phrase:
Not just molded. Completed.
Visual direction:
Show CNC trimming, bonding inserts, assembly details, paint booth, clear-coated carbon, primer-ready parts or final fitment.
